data.description: Beat the market and these rates! The seller has an assumable mortgage with Freedom Mortage for around 225k at a 3.25% rate that you can take over and pay the difference. Take this spacious 2428 sq ft Highland plan showcasing a thoughtfully designed layout. With 3 bedrooms, 2 1/2 baths, a 2-car garage, and a basement, this home offers plenty of room for comfortable living.   Step into the kitchen and be amazed by the exquisite designer cabinets, recessed can lighting, and ample counter space. Stainless steel appliances and a convenient pantry add a touch of luxury. Plus, enjoy the option of an extra refrigerator if desired.    The kitchen seamlessly transitions into the breakfast and family room areas, with an island providing a perfect spot for gathering. You'll love the flexible front room, which can be customized to suit your lifestyle - whether you prefer a living room, office, or dining room.    Upstairs, discover 3 inviting bedrooms and a charming loft space. The primary suite boasts a large walk-in closet and a deluxe primary bath, complete with a transom window, linen closet, and dual bowl vanity.    Take advantage of the electrical rough-in for ceiling fans in the family room and master suite, ensuring comfort all year round. Large windows flood the home with abundant natural light, creating a warm and inviting atmosphere.    Situated in the esteemed Fall Creek community, this home is truly a hidden gem. Notably, the property is equipped with solar panels, which contribute to an astounding average electric bill of just $20.00 per month. Additionally, a 1-year home warranty offers peace of mind.    All this is near shopping and restaurants. Expressway entrance at 30 or 52 with 3 train options within 20 to 30 minutes of home.    Don't miss out on the opportunity to make this charming home your own. Contact us today to schedule a viewing and experience the delightful benefits firsthand. The seller is willing to help with $3,000.00 in Closing costs. Ask about lenders to fill the gap on the balance and purchase price today. Must qualify for assumable with lean holder. Most 2nds if needed are 10% down and have to qualify for too. Call with questions.
